features: Meets & exceeds recommended daily allowance – In order to support optimal health and well-being, you need a science-based dose of vitamins and minerals every day. Our Two-Per-Day Multivitamin meets or exceeds the Recommended Dietary Allowance (RDA) for nearly every ingredient where an RDA exists, for both common and hard-to-get nutrients, like biotin, vitamin A through vitamin E, and even iodine, thiamine and selenium.

Support immune health with vitamins C & D – Vitamin C is associated with immune system health, which may be due to its ability to scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress, as well as its stimulation of the production and function of white blood cells. Vitamin D3 supports immune system health, bone health and more.

Get the most from your multivitamin – Everyone should be getting the most out of their daily multivitamin. There's no simpler way to ensure your body is getting the essential vitamins, minerals and nutrients it needs to support your health. But not all multivitamins are created equal, so choose our best wellness formula for overall health: Two-Per-Day Multivitamin.

Ingredients matter – Sourced using only the finest raw ingredients with the purity and potency your body deserves. The majority of our products are non-GMO, gluten-free and manufactured in the USA—and a Certificate of Analysis is available for every product we produce.

Live your healthiest life – For over 40 years, we’ve been developing advanced, effective formulas made with the highest standards and based on the latest scientific findings. We believe the answers to a healthier, richer life are within reach, and that rigorous scientific research is the path to get us there. That’s why so many of our nutritional formulas are designed using specific ingredients and amounts based on scientific studies.
body.description: Staying healthy is a daily effort. Two-Per-Day Multivitamin makes it easy. This customer favorite wellness formula includes over 25 different vitamins, minerals and extracts. From more common vitamins (including the B vitamins like vitamin B6 and vitamin B12), along with health favorites vitamin C and vitamin D3, to healthy minerals and extracts (including zinc, selenium, inositol, apigenin, boron and more), our Two-Per-Day daily multivitamin is a comprehensive formula that supports a healthy foundation with quality ingredients.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Revitalize Your Health and Boost Your Energy with Life Extension's Two-Per-Day Capsules
reviews.reviewText: As for the Two-Per-Day Capsules, they truly live up to their name. Packed with a comprehensive blend of essential vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants, these capsules provide a convenient and efficient way to support overall health and wellbeing. What sets them apart is the attention to detail in formulating the optimal dosages of each nutrient, ensuring that you receive the right balance of ingredients for maximum effectiveness. I particularly appreciate the inclusion of key nutrients like vitamin D, B vitamins, and selenium, which are often lacking in our diets and play crucial roles in maintaining vitality.What truly impressed me about these capsules is the noticeable impact they had on my energy levels and overall vitality. After incorporating them into my daily routine, I experienced a significant boost in my energy levels throughout the day, allowing me to stay focused and productive. Moreover, the capsules are easy to swallow and free from any unpleasant aftertaste, making them a hassle-free addition to my morning routine. I also appreciate the fact that they are formulated without unnecessary fillers or artificial additives, which aligns with my commitment to prioritizing clean and natural products.In conclusion, the Two-Per-Day Capsules from Life Extension are a game-changer when it comes to comprehensive daily supplementation. From the informative website and easy ordering process to the impressive results I experienced, every aspect of my experience with this product has been exceptional. If you're looking for a reliable, high-quality supplement to support your overall health and wellbeing, I highly recommend giving these capsules a try. They have certainly become a staple in my wellness routine, and I'm confident they will have a positive impact on anyone who incorporates them into their daily regimen.

reviews.reviewText: These pills smell SO BAD. Like urine.Within thirty minutes of taking im having terrible "pee smelling burps".Sometimes I gag trying to take them.But! These are the real deal. I feel noticeably better within twenty minutes of taking them. To avoid the yucky burps I've been having a scoop of peanut butter before or after I've taken them.If you have an upset stomach from the pills try a piece of toast right before or after taking them.Regardless of the strong smell my entire family is taking these. Because a stinky smell is worth having double the brain power and a lot more energy throughout our day.I've been adding these to my mother's daily regiment as well and she said it makes her feel less pain, (arthritis, rotator cuff microtears, memory fog, and somewhat better sleep). reviews.reviewText: I use many life extension supplements. I was looking for a high-dose multivitamin and like the amounts listed on the bottle. However I am older and maybe that's why these are a little rough on my stomach. I take only one per day because they make me feel nauseated unless I take them in the middle of a substantial meal. I would recommend them for their quality and ingredients.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A good formula is hard to find
reviews.reviewText: When it comes to a broad-spectrum daily multivitamin, finding a good formula can be a challenge and none of them are perfect. Between what it contains, the amounts of what it contains, and the sources they are derived from, this is about the best you can do unless you are willing to spend quite a lot. As a two a day formula I recommend taking them separately and with food. There is a bit of vitamin burp and taste. I've seen some expensive three a day formulas that are probably better, but that point you might as well put together a comprehensive many pills per day regiment. If you want to keep it simple without breaking the bank, this is a solid choice.
